-- 
German Firms Increased Foreign Direct Investment, UNCTAD Says

-- B y   C o r n e l i u s   R a h n
-- 
2011-07-27T05:10:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-27/german-firms-increased-foreign-direct-investment-unctad-says.html
German companies advanced to second
place in terms of  foreign direct investment  last year behind
U.S. firms, passing French and outspending Chinese companies,
according to a  report  from the United Nations Conference on
Trade and Development.  FDI by German firms rose 35 percent to $105 billion, while
French companies invested $84 billion, 18 percent less than a
year earlier, according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cornelius Rahn in Frankfurt at 
 crahn2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kenneth Wong in Berlin at 
 kwong11@bloomberg.net  